LEX Escrow.

"Payer" is a person.
"Seller" is a person.
"Arbiter" is a person.
"Amount" is an amount.

The Payer pays an Amount into escrow, appoints the Seller, appoints the Arbiter.

CLAUSE: Pay Out.
The Arbiter may pay the escrow to the Seller.

CLAUSE: Pay Back.
The Arbiter may pay the escrow to the Payer.

